* When forming compounds (typically 4 or 5 morae in length), it usually functions as a deaccenting suffix ({{m|ja|[[平板化]][[接尾辞]]|tr=heibanka setsubiji}}). This results in a ''[[heiban]]'' (Type 0) pitch accent pattern for the entire compound, regardless of the original accent of the base noun.

